net.coderodde.stat

Class AbstractProbabilityDistribution<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.coderodde.stat.AbstractProbabilityDistribution<E>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArrayProbabilityDistribution, BinarySearchProbabilityDistribution, BinaryTreeProbabilityDistribution, LinkedListProbabilityDistribution

    public abstract class AbstractProbabilityDistribution<E>
extends Object
    This class implements an abstract base class for probability distributions. Elements are added with strictly positive weights and whenever asking this data structure for a random element, their respective weights are taken into account. For example, if this data structure contains three different elements (a, b, c with respective weights 1.0, 1.0, 3.0), whenever asking for a random element, there is 20 percent chance of obtaining a, 20 percent chance of obtaining b, and 60 percent chance of obtaining c.
    Version:
    1.6 (Jun 11, 2016)
    Author:
    Rodion "rodde" Efremov
